trans-unit.source: Supports a simple iteration over a <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: Støtter en enkel gjentakelse over en <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: Den `foreach` -setningen for språket C# (`for each` i Visual Basic) skjuler kompleks enumeratorene.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: Ved hjelp av derfor `foreach` anbefales, i stedet for direkte manipulering enumeratoren.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratorene kan brukes til å lese data i samlingen, men de kan ikke brukes til å endre den underliggende samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: I utgangspunktet er enumeratoren plassert før det første elementet i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>henter også enumeratoren tilbake til denne plasseringen.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: På dette Plasser, kaller <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>oppstår det et unntak.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Du må derfor kalle <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>å flytte enumeratoren til det første elementet i samlingen før leser <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>Returnerer det samme objektet før enten <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>eller <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>angir <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>til neste element.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>formidler slutten av samlingen enumeratoren er plassert etter det siste elementet i samlingen og <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerer `false`.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: Når enumeratoren er på denne plasseringen, etterfølgende kall til <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>også returnere `false`.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: Hvis siste kall til <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerte `false`, kall <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>oppstår det et unntak.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Angi <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>til det første elementet i samlingen på nytt, kan du kalle <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>etterfulgt av <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: En opplisting forblir gyldig så lenge samlingen forblir uendret.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du endrer til samlingen, for eksempel å legge til, endre eller slette elementer, ugyldiggjøres, enumeratoren og neste kall eller <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>oppstår en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the element that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: Hvis samlingen er endret mellom <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>og <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>returnerer elementet som det, selv om enumeratoren ugyldiggjøres allerede.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratoren har ikke eksklusiv tilgang til samlingen. lister opp i en samling er derfor gjelder ikke en sikker-prosedyre.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: Selv når en samling synkroniseres, kan andre tråder fortsatt endre samlingen, som fører til at enumeratoren til Iverksett et unntak.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: For å garantere tråd sikkerhetsnivået under opplisting, kan du låse samlingen under hele opplistingen eller opp unntak som er et resultat av endringer foretatt av andre tråder.

trans-unit.source: Gets the current element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Henter gjeldende element i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: After an enumerator is created or after a <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> must be called to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of Current; otherwise, Current is undefined.
trans-unit.target: Når en opplisting som er opprettet eller etter et <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>må kalles for å gå videre enumeratoren til det første elementet i samlingen før lese verdien for gjeldende; ellers gjeldende er udefinert.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: Current also throws an exception if the last call to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, which indicates the end of the collection.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende også oppstår det et unntak hvis siste kall til <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>returnerte `false`, noe som angir slutten av samlingen.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: Current does not move the position of the enumerator, and consecutive calls to Current return the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende flyttes ikke plasseringen av enumeratoren og etterfølgende kall til gjeldende returnere det samme objektet før enten <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>eller <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: En opplisting forblir gyldig så lenge samlingen forblir uendret.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis du endrer til samlingen, for eksempel å legge til, endre eller slette elementer, ugyldiggjøres, enumeratoren og neste kall eller <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A>oppstår en <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The current element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende element i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: The enumerator is positioned before the first element of the collection or after the last element.
trans-unit.target: Enumeratoren er plassert før det første elementet i samlingen, eller etter siste element.

trans-unit.source: Advances the enumerator to the next element of the collection.
trans-unit.target: Flytter enumeratoren til neste element i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: After an enumerator is created or after a <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called, an enumerator is positioned before the first element of the collection, and the first call to MoveNext moves the enumerator over the first element of the collection.
trans-unit.target: Når en opplisting som er opprettet eller etter et <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>er kalt, en opplisting som er plassert før det første elementet i samlingen, og det første kallet til MoveNext flytter enumeratoren over det første elementet i samlingen.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: If MoveNext passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and MoveNext returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: Hvis MoveNext sender slutten av samlingen enumeratoren er plassert etter det siste elementet i samlingen og MoveNext returnerer `false`.

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to MoveNext also return `false` until <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: Når enumeratoren på denne plasseringen, etterfølgende kall til MoveNext også returnere `false` før <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>kalles.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: Sets the enumerator to its initial position, which is before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: Angir enumeratoren til den opprinnelige posisjonen, som er før det første elementet i samlingen.

trans-unit.source: Reset moves the enumerator to the beginning of the collection, before the first element.
trans-unit.target: Tilbakestill flytter enumeratoren til starten av samlingen, før det første elementet.

trans-unit.source: After Reset, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> must be called to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.
